parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Throttle Cable/Linkage Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cable or linkage can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the accelerator pedal bracket can cause the pedal to break off or stick to the floor, leading to unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: Pedal breaks off or sticks to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body cable can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.

The failure of the Airbag Controller Card (ACC) can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to unexpected airbag deployments or failures to deploy in the event of a crash, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on intermittently
the airbag light remains solidly illuminated
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
and the motorized seatbelt does not retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to unexpected airbag deployments or failures to deploy in the event of a crash, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
and the seatbelt sensor is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to unexpected airbag deployments or failures to deploy in the event of a crash, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the motorized seatbelt does not retract
and the seatbelt fails to lock in place during a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially lead to accidents due to loss of engine power.
symptoms: oil leaking from the bottom of the vehicle
oil leaking from the engine timing cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: vehicle loses power and catches erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially lead to carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: white smoke coming from the exhaust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, and potentially lead to accidents due to loss of engine power.
symptoms: Cooling fan blade hits the radiator

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical and sensor issues can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially lead to engine damage.
Power steering and mounting issues can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: Power steering bracket not mounted to the cylinder head block

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt system can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the inability to properly restrain occupants.
symptoms: The seat belt light comes on and stays on intermittently
the belt tightens or loosens unexpectedly
the emergency release button does not work
the belt chokes or traps the occupant.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Latch Failure Affecting Automatic Seat Belts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the automatic seat belt system to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the inability to properly restrain occupants.
symptoms: the door does not lock or shut properly
the automatic seat belt does not function correctly
the sensor that operates the belts is defective.
